When looking at a commit

{code}
https://bitbucket.example.com/projects/XXX/repos/myrepo/browse/path/to/somefile?at=MYSHA1
{code}

one can click &#x27;blame&#x27; button to see the annotations (equivalent to {{git blame}}), but it should have an option to ignore white space changes (equivalent to {{git blame -w}}). It seems very easy to implement.

I have multiple repos using the cameCase naming convention.\\
